text.tspan: Daily new estimated COVID-19 infections from the YYG model, United
Estimates of the true number of infections. The "upper" and "lower" lines show the bounds of a 95% uncertainty interval.
For comparison, confirmed cases are infections that have been confirmed with a test.
Data source: Youyang Gu (2020); World Health Organization (2025)
Note: This chart shows the model estimates as of 4 October 2020. YYG announced that this is the final model update.
